Plotting the most frequent words

The most frequently used 20 words (after removing stopwords) are taken as output from Python environment into csv files.

library(ggplot2)

Top 20 words used by BUSH

bush = read.csv('C:/Users/Hello/Documents/R workspace/textclassification/outfile_bush.csv')
ggplot(bush,aes(x=word,y=count))+geom_bar(stat='identity')+geom_text(aes(label=count))+theme(axis.text.x =element_text(size  = 10,angle = 45,hjust = 1,vjust = 1))
